        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(net): conditionalize proxyTls only for HTTPS proxies to fix Telegram plugin proxy issues",
        "body": "### Summary\nFixes an issue in the Telegram plugin where using SOCKS5 or plain HTTP proxies resulted in immediate connection failure with `ECONNRESET`. This was caused by `createHttp1ProxyAgent` unconditionally setting `proxyTls: true`. This patch conditionally sets `proxyTls` to `true` only if the proxy URL protocol starts with `https:`.\n\n### Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Telegram plugin connection failures when using SOCKS5 or HTTP proxies.\nReal environment tested: Linux with SOCKS5 proxy server.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Run proxy connection requests using createHttp1ProxyAgent with a SOCKS5 proxy protocol scheme.\nEvidence after fix: Connection completes successfully instead of returning ECONNRESET.\nObserved result after fix: Undici no longer attempts TLS handshake on non-HTTPS proxies, allowing socks5/http proxy channels to establish successfully.\nWhat was not tested: Performance implications under extremely high concurrency (not expected to change).\n",
